================================================================================
PHASE 4 — DATABASE AND ROLE ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================
Goal: Design the full PostgreSQL schema in Supabase. Apply Row Level Security.
      Define all roles and their permissions. Generate migration files.

--- 4.1  Core Tables ---

[x] profiles       — id, email, full_name, role, is_active, created_at, updated_at
[x] sessions       — id, owner_id, name, description, capacity, starts_at, ends_at, is_active
[x] tickets        — id, session_id, token (unique), attendee_name/email, is_used, used_at, scanned_by, expires_at
[x] scan_logs      — id, ticket_id, session_id, scanned_by, scan_result, scanned_at, ip_address, user_agent
[x] staff_invitations — id, email, invited_by, session_id, token (unique), accepted_at, expires_at

--- 4.2  Indexes ---
[x] idx_tickets_token      ON tickets(token)
[x] idx_tickets_session    ON tickets(session_id)
[x] idx_tickets_is_used    ON tickets(is_used)
[x] idx_scan_logs_ticket   ON scan_logs(ticket_id)
[x] idx_scan_logs_scanned_at ON scan_logs(scanned_at)
[x] idx_scan_logs_session  ON scan_logs(session_id)
[x] idx_sessions_owner     ON sessions(owner_id)
[x] idx_profiles_role      ON profiles(role)

--- 4.3  Row Level Security ---
[x] RLS enabled on all 5 tables

[x] profiles RLS:
      - read own row (auth.uid() = id)
      - owners read all (get_my_role() = 'owner')
      - update own row
      - INSERT/DELETE via service role only

[x] sessions RLS:
      - owners full CRUD on own sessions
      - scanners SELECT active sessions

[x] tickets RLS:
      - owners full CRUD on their session's tickets
      - scanners SELECT only (no direct UPDATE — must go through API)

[x] scan_logs RLS:
      - owners SELECT logs for their sessions
      - scanners SELECT own logs
      - no UPDATE or DELETE policy = immutable

[x] staff_invitations RLS:
      - owners full CRUD on invitations they created
      - anyone can SELECT by token (for accept-invite page)

--- 4.4  Database Functions ---
[x] validate_ticket(p_token, p_scanner_id) — SECURITY DEFINER, atomic
      FOR UPDATE NOWAIT lock → prevents race condition double-scans
      Returns: valid/not_found/already_used/expired/collision
[x] handle_new_user() trigger — auto-creates profile on auth.users INSERT
[x] handle_updated_at() trigger — auto-updates updated_at on profiles + sessions
[x] get_my_role() helper — SECURITY DEFINER, used by RLS policies (no recursion)

--- 4.5  Migration Files ---
[!] supabase login + link still needed for CLI migrations
    Schema was applied directly via SQL editor — functionally identical
[!] Run after supabase login: supabase gen types typescript --linked > src/types/database.ts

--- 4.6  Phase 4 Verification Checklist ---
[x] SQL ran successfully — "No rows returned" ✅
[x] All 5 tables created
[x] RLS enabled on all tables
[x] validate_ticket function created with SECURITY DEFINER
[x] All indexes created
[x] Triggers created (handle_new_user, handle_updated_at)
[x] get_my_role() helper function created

EXPECTED RESULT: A locked-down, indexed, audit-ready schema where no client
can bypass validation logic. All writes go through controlled server paths.

TROUBLESHOOTING:
  - RLS blocking legitimate reads → check policy conditions carefully
  - Function not found → confirm SECURITY DEFINER and correct schema
  - Type mismatch → regen types after schema change

