================================================================================
PHASE 11 — SECURITY HARDENING
================================================================================
Goal: Make the app resistant to common web attacks and fraud vectors.

--- 11.1  API Security Headers ---
[x] Add to next.config.js headers():
      X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
      X-Frame-Options: DENY
      X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
      Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
      Permissions-Policy: camera=(self), microphone=()
      Content-Security-Policy: (strict, allow supabase CDN)

--- 11.2  Rate Limiting ---
[x] /api/validate: 30 req/min per user + 60/min per IP (dual layer)
[x] /api/auth/login: 5 attempts/min per IP
[x] Shared checkRateLimit() utility in src/lib/rate-limit.ts
[x] Return 429 with Retry-After header

--- 11.3  Input Sanitization ---
[x] All API inputs validated through Zod schemas
[x] Reject unexpected fields (use Zod .strict()) — all schemas updated
[x] Never pass raw user input to SQL (Supabase client uses parameterized queries)

--- 11.4  QR Token Hardening ---
[x] Tokens are UUID v4 (122 bits of entropy) — cannot be guessed
[x] HMAC-SHA256 signature added to QR payload (src/lib/qr/hmac.ts)
    Set HMAC_SECRET env var in production to enable; graceful skip in dev
[x] Signature verified in /api/validate before hitting DB

--- 11.5  Session / Cookie Security ---
[x] Supabase SSR uses httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookies automatically
[x] Session expiry handled by Supabase Auth

--- 11.6  Dependency Audit ---
[x] pnpm audit — 0 vulnerabilities (PostCSS patched via pnpm-workspace.yaml override)
[x] Review Supabase RLS policies after any schema change

--- 11.7  Penetration Test Checklist ---
[x] Try to access /api/validate without auth → should get 401
[x] Try to submit a random token → should get not_found, no info leak
[x] Try to scan as owner → should work (owner has scanner rights too)
[x] Try to use a revoked scanner account → should get 403
[x] Try SQL injection via payload field → Zod + parameterized queries block it
[x] Try to enumerate ticket tokens → rate limiting blocks bulk attempts

--- 11.8  Phase 11 Verification Checklist ---
[x] Security headers present (check with securityheaders.com in production)
[x] Rate limiting on login and validate routes
[x] All Zod schemas have .strict()
[x] pnpm audit shows 0 vulnerabilities

